James Lewis & Martin Fowler published "microservices"
martinfowler.com/articles/microservices.html

microservices = divided, separate processes, talk between each others

maintainability at scale
independently scalable
freedom of technology

microservices are good if a codebase is too big for one person
are you ready to build a distributed system?

"multi-lith": monolith + some microservices

builtins extensions:
GET/POST
AMQP RPC
AMQP pub Sub
Timer
Websockets (experimental)

you can build your own extension

